@NODE "Introduction"

"TimeSaver.rexx" is an ARexx script to auto-adjust inaccurate internal
battery clocks.
The reason I wrote this little program was that my internal A4000 clock
runs about 2 seconds too slow per day. I was eventually too lazy to adjust
my clock every few days to keep an accurate time. {I guess it IS true:
We Germans are all very punctual ;-}.
From version 1.1 it also auto-switches between daylight-saving times, but
currently only works for the european switching days (last sundays in
march/october).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Disclaimer"

